; 490-430 BC: Empedocles

* Everything is composed of a heterogeneous mixture of the elements (earth, water, air, and fire) via the dialectic between the positive, constructive attraction of love, and the negative, deconstructive repulsion of strife.
* The origins of all minds are due to pure luck, yet they are ~~comically~~ karmically punished.
* In order to perceive anything at all, the elements of an object (e.g. properties and light) must correspondingly and representatively inhere in us as a subject.